{{Infobox language |name=Inga Kichwa |nativename=''Ingano'' |states=[[Colombia]] |speakers=33,000 |date=2007–2008 |ref=e18 |familycolor=American |fam1=[[Quechua languages|Quechua]] |fam2=[[Quechua II languages|Quechua II]] |fam3=[[Northern Quechua|Northern]] |fam4=[[Kichwa language|Kichwa]] |lc1=inb |ld1=Highland Inga |lc2=inj |ld2=Jungle Inga |glotto=inga1251 |glottorefname=Ingan Quechua IIB }}
'''Inga Kichwa''' is a dialect of [[Kichwa]] spoken in the [[Colombia]]n [[Putumayo Department|Putumayo]] region by the [[Inga people]]. There are two dialects: Highland Inga, spoken in the [[Sibundoy]] valley; and Jungle Inga, spoken on the [[Putumayo River|Putumayo]] and [[Japurá River]]s. ''Ethnologue'' 16 reports Highland Inga is partially intelligible with Imbabura [[Kichwa]].
