{{see also|List of Malayalam language authors|Malayalam Literary Awards}} '''[[Sahitya Akademi Award]]''' is given each year, since 1955, by [[Sahitya Akademi]] ([[India]]'s National Academy of Letters), to Indian writers for their outstanding books of literary merit published in any of the 24 major Indian languages. The list of [[Malayalam|Malayalam language]] writers who have won the award is given below.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.prd.kerala.gov.in/awards.htm |title=Kendra Sahitya Academy Awards (Malayalam) |publisher=Public Relations Department, [[Government of Kerala]] |accessdate=11 April 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070524212356/http://www.prd.kerala.gov.in/awards.htm |archivedate=24 May 2007 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Akademi Awards (1955-2015)|url=http://sahitya-akademi.gov.in/sahitya-akademi/awards/akademi%20samman_suchi.jsp|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304084937/http://sahitya-akademi.gov.in/sahitya-akademi/awards/akademi%20samman_suchi.jsp|archive-date=4 March 2016|publisher=[[Sahitya Akademi]]|accessdate=4 March 2016}}</ref>
