{{Infobox language |name=Marovo |region=[[Solomon Islands]] |speakers={{sigfig|8090|2}} |date=1999 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Austronesian |fam2=[[Malayo-Polynesian languages|Malayo-Polynesian]] |fam3=[[Oceanic languages|Oceanic]] |fam4=[[Northwest Solomonic languages|Northwest Solomonic]] |fam5=New Georgia – Ysabel |fam6=[[New Georgia languages|New Georgia]] |iso3=mvo |glotto=maro1244 |glottorefname=Marovo }}
'''Marovo''' is an [[Austronesian language]] of the [[Solomon Islands]]. It is spoken in the [[New Georgia Group]] on islands in [[Marovo Lagoon]] and on the neighbouring islands of [[New Georgia]], [[Vangunu]] and [[Nggatokae]]. The usual [[word order]] in sentences is [[verb]]-[[subject (grammar)|subject]]-[[object (grammar)|object]].
Names for local [[fauna]] are similar to but still much distinct from those in [[Roviana (language)|Roviana]] (and presumably other [[New Georgia languages]]).<ref>Read & Moseby (2006)</ref>
== External links == * Materials on Marovo are included in the open access [[Arthur Capell]] collections ([http://catalog.paradisec.org.au/collections/AC1 AC1] and [http://catalog.paradisec.org.au/collections/AC2 AC2]) held by [[Paradisec]]
