{{Infobox language |name=Mire |nativename=Mulgi |states=[[Chad]] |region=Southwest |speakers=5,000 |date=2011 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Afro-Asiatic |fam2=[[Chadic languages|Chadic]] |fam3=[[East Chadic languages|East Chadic]] |fam4=[[East Chadic A languages|East Chadic A]] |fam5=[[Sibine languages|Sibine]] (A.1.1) |iso3=mvh |glotto=mire1238 |glottorefname=Mire }}
'''Mire''', or '''Mulgi''', is an [[Afro-Asiatic languages|Afro-Asiatic]] language spoken in the southwestern [[Chad]]ian prefectures of [[Tandjile Prefecture]] and [[Lai Prefecture]].<ref name=e18/> Most of the speakers, who generally practice traditional religions or [[Christianity]], speak [[Ndam language|Ndam]] (65% [[lexical similarity]]) or [[Kimré language|Kimré]] (32% lexical similarity) as a second language.
