{{Infobox language |name=Sanglechi |nativename=''Dargi'' |states=[[Afghanistan]], [[Tajikistan]] |speakers=2,200 |date=2009 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Indo-European |fam2=[[Indo-Iranian languages|Indo-Iranian]] |fam3=[[Iranian languages|Iranian]] |fam4=[[Eastern Iranian languages|Eastern]] |fam5=[[Sanglechi–Ishkashimi language|Sanglechi–Ishkashimi]] |script=None |iso3=sgy |lc1=wrd|ld1=Warduji (duplicate code)<ref>Hammarström (2015) Ethnologue 16/17/18th editions: a comprehensive review: online appendices</ref> |glotto=sang1317 |glottoname=Sanglechi |glotto2=sang1318 |glottoname2=Sanglich |glotto3=zeba1237 |glottoname3=Zebak |lingua=58-ABD-db }}
'''Sanglechi''' is an [[Iranian languages|Iranian language]] spoken in two villages in the [[Zebak District]] of [[Afghanistan]]. It is also spoken in [[Tajikistan]], where it is called '''Sanglich'''. The name comes from the Sanglech valley in which many of the people live; the name Warduji, after the [[Werdoge River|Werdoge Valley]] is also used.
