==Grammar==
===Morphology===
====Reduplication==== Yapese makes use of [[reduplication]] for several morphological functions, including deriving stative adjectives from inchoative adjectives, as in (1a–b), as well as to make [[Diminutive|diminutives]] of verbs, as in (2a-b) {{r|Jensen1977|p=112-114}}:
:{{interlinear| number = (1a) | roow | become.red | 'to become red' }}
:{{interlinear | number = (1b) | roow~roow | STAT~red | 'to be red' }}
:{{interlinear | number = (2a) | toey | chop | 'to chop' }}
:{{interlinear | number = (2b) | si-toey~toey | DIM-DIM~chop | 'to chop a little' }}
====Pronouns==== Yapese distinguishes between three [[Grammatical number|numbers]] (singular, dual, and plural) and three [[Grammatical person|persons]] (first, second, and third), as well as [[Clusivity|clusivity]] in its personal pronouns {{r|Jensen1977|p=134}}.
{| class="wikitable" style="text-align:center" |+ Yapese independent personal pronouns |- ! ! Singular ! Dual ! Plural |- | 1.INCL | | ''gadow'' | ''gadaed'' |- | 1.EXCL | ''gaeg'' | ''gamow'' | ''gamaed'' |- | 2 | ''guur'' | ''gimeew'' | ''gimeed'' |- | 3 | ''qiir'' | ''yow'' | ''yaed'' |}
